cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC 

The paper deals with a problem of distributed channel allocation in large networks, which involves game theoretic formulations and performance measurement. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory and Economics). The problem also involves interference channels, which suggests the category cs.NI (Computer Science - Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses achievable rates, which is related to the category cs.IT (Computer Science - Information Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes a modified Fictitious Play algorithm, which is related to the category cs.SI (Computer Science - Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with distributed algorithms, which suggests the category cs.DC (Computer Science - Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
